th Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The second half\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1622}, {\"ngram\": \"wave\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1631}, {\"ngram\": \"wave\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1642}, {\"ngram\": \"the Blitzboks' defence\", \"from\": 1661, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"terriers\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1723}, {\"ngram\": \"mistakes\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1747}, {\"ngram\": \"possession\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1786}, {\"ngram\": \"the deal\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1828}, {\"ngram\": \"their best performances\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"the season\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier on Thursday, South Africa smashed Japan by 49-5 to sneak into the quarter-finals.\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1902, \"end\": 1914, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"score\": 0.9998982371393881, \"rank\": 0.00010177321726535178, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_sevens_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1923, \"end\": 1928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9979616706461214, \"rank\": 0.0020371130410022547, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Thursday\", \"from\": 1892, \"to\": 1900}, {\"ngram\": \"the quarter-finals\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Springbok Sevens team had a 35-0 lead at the break in their final Pool A match, scoring five tries in the first half and adding two more after the break.\", \"from\": 1971, \"to\": 2128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Springbok Sevens\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a 35-0 lead\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 2016, \"to\": 2025}, {\"ngram\": \"their final Pool A match\", \"from\": 2029, \"to\": 2053}, {\"ngram\": \"five tries\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2073}, {\"ngram\": \"the first half\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2091}, {\"ngram\": \"the break\", \"from\": 2118, \"to\": 2127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Blitzboks, who had to replace the injured Quewin Nortje with Ronald Brown on the second day, knew they had to win by at least 21 points to make into the final eight and did just that.\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2317, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2195, \"end\": 2207, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ron_Brown\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.1875099029516117e-22, \"text\": \"Ronald Brown\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ron_Brown\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ron_Brown\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Blitzboks\", \"from\": 2130, \"to\": 2143}, {\"ngram\": \"the injured Quewin Nortje\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2189}, {\"ngram\": \"the second day\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2225}, {\"ngram\": \"at least 21 points\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were ruthless in the opening half and scored almost at will, dominating the restarts, possession and territory.\", \"from\": 2318, \"to\": 2434, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening half\", \"from\": 2340